3625
03:40:06,580 --> 03:40:10,180
Like your browser can't read your password manager's memory and vice versa.

3626
03:40:10,400 --> 03:40:13,580
They live in parallel universes that only the kernel can see between.

3627
03:40:13,580 --> 03:40:21,800
Pretty cool, but the MMU also caches recent translations in a tiny structure called the TLB, the Translation Look-Aside Buffer.

3628
03:40:21,940 --> 03:40:25,280
A translation, meaning a virtual address mapped to a physical address.

3629
03:40:25,420 --> 03:40:34,220
When a program touches a page that isn't in RAM, the MMU raises a page fault, which wakes the kernel up and loads a page from disk and resumes the program like nothing happened.

